// Project-local Zed settings for af.
//
// The host's Zed installation ships Prettier 3.8.3 and, by default, runs
// it as the on-save formatter for Markdown files. Prettier's default
// markdown handling rewrites nested-list continuation indents (4 -> 2
// spaces) and collapses some bullet-continuation whitespace. That
// silently rewrites TODO.md, PROGRESS.md, and CHANGELOG.md every time
// they are opened or auto-saved, producing semantically meaningless
// diffs that mask real edits.
//
// We deliberately keep the project's markdown formatting consistent
// with the rest of the repo's house style (see .editorconfig). Turning
// `format_on_save` off for Markdown here means Zed will leave .md
// files exactly as written. The `.prettierignore` at the repo root
// is the belt-and-suspenders for other tools that might invoke
// Prettier (pre-commit hooks, CI lint, other editors).
//
// If you ever want to opt back in for a specific file, run
// `prettier --write <file>` manually and inspect the diff.
{
  "languages": {
    "Markdown": {
      "format_on_save": "off",
      "remove_trailing_whitespace_on_save": true,
      "ensure_final_newline_on_save": true
    }
  }
}
